"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-how-to-watch-paralympics-2024-free-tv-channel-live-stream-b1178446.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  TheParisParalympicsbegin today, offeringTeam GBmore chances to win medals this summer.  After a stunning Olympic Games in Paris, the action starts in the French capital following what promises to be another dramatic opening ceremony.  Great Britain finished second at the delayed Tokyo Games last time out and have now been set a target of 100-140 medals by UK Sport.  Here's everything you need to know about where to watch.  TV channel:The live action can be watched free-to-air in the UK on Channel 4, which has promised more than 1,300 hours of coverage.  The broadcaster is currently showing documentaries to pave the way and will be showing the coverage on television and online.  Unlike at the Olympics, where the BBC had only limited broadcasting, Channel 4 will be showing every event with up to 18 streams accessible online.  There will also be a nightly highlights show.  Live stream:Channel 4's website and app will provide a free live stream service online.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Football  Arsenal: Jurrien Timber named in Netherlands squad ahead of Carabao Cup final amid Mikel Arteta update  Arsenal star named in squad ahead of Carabao Cup final  5  World  Iran missile attack on UK-US Diego Garcia military base raises fears London could be within striking distance  Iran fires ballistic missiles at UK-US base on Diego Garcia\"}"